to release steam. Bake for 30-40 minutes (190°C) until golden brown.","step":6},{"isHeader":false,"content":"Leave to rest for 10 minutes before serving - works well with custard, cream or ice cream.","step":7}],"usefulItems":"cling film, rolling pin, shallow metal pie dish or shallow tart tin (Ø 23 cm), pastry brush, refrigerator, oven","id":"r140558","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-29zQJGZfNkQ\/XZWfkuF130I\/AAAAAAAAfGo\/T1r-kFgs25I61WNZAz2hO0c7QK2Or5U0ACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_xhTvlqsp-xST0BYd.png","title":"Cherry Pie with Pistachio Pastry","ingredients":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Ingredients"},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Pistachio Puff Pastry"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"50 g pistachio nuts, unsalted, shelled"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"200 g unsalted butter, diced (1 cm) then frozen for 30 minutes"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"175 g plain flour, plus extra for dusting"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"1 pinch fine sea salt"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"6 Tbsp water, cold"},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Cherry Filling"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"650 g tinned pitted black cherries, in syrup, drained"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"100 g caster sugar"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"25 g tapioca starch"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"2 Tbsp lemon juice"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"¼ tsp vanilla extract"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"1 egg, beaten, for glazing"}],"nutrition":["per 1 portion","2383 kJ \/ 570 kcal","6.4 g","62.9 g","32.5 g"],"hintsAndTricks":["Cherries make a lovely rich pie filling, and the nutty puff pastry used here adds an extra dimension and means that the end result isn’t too dense. Serve warm with custard, cream or ice cream."],"basicInfo":["medium","15m","2h","6 portions"]}